doc.after: Colombia s varied cuisine is influenced by its diverse fauna and flora as well as the cultural traditions of the ethnic groups Colombian dishes and ingredients vary widely by region Some of the most common ingredients are cereals such as rice and maize tubers such as potato and cassava assorted legumes meats including beef chicken pork and goat fish and seafood Colombia cuisine also features a variety of tropical fruits such as cape gooseberry feijoa araz dragon fruit mangostino granadilla papaya guava mora blackberry lulo soursop and passionfruit 236 237
